# Content collections — Zeroindex

Schemas are defined only in `src/content.config.ts`. Each collection uses a `glob` loader with the base folder under `src/content/`.

| Collection    | Folder                      | Format   | Required / notable fields |
|---------------|-----------------------------|----------|---------------------------|
| `integrations`| `integrations/`             | `.md`    | `email`, `integration`, `description`, `permissions[]`, `details[]`, `logo.url` (`image()`), `logo.alt`, `tags[]` |
| `docs`        | `docs/`                     | `.md`/`.mdx` | `title`, `description`, `category`; optional `order`, `lastUpdated` |
| `legal`       | `legal/`                    | `.md`    | `page`, `pubDate` |
| `changelog`   | `changelog/`                | `.md`    | `page`, `description`, `pubDate`, `image.url` (`image()`), `image.alt` |
| `team`        | `team/`                     | `.md`    | `name`, `image.url` (`image()`), `image.alt`; optional `role`, `bio`, `socials` |
| `posts`       | `posts/`                    | `.md`    | `title`, `pubDate`, `description`, `team` (must match a **`team` entry id**), `image.url` (`image()`), `image.alt`, `tags[]` |

**IDs:** Derived from file path (e.g. `team/david-lee.md` → id `david-lee`; `docs/getting-started/introduction.mdx` → `getting-started/introduction`). MDX docs use `generateId` stripping the extension.

**Images:** For `image()` fields, follow existing entries — paths like `/src/images/blog/...`, `/src/images/integrations/...`, etc. Do not switch to broken or external paths for required `image()` refs without verifying Astro accepts them.

**Templates:** Clone an existing file in the same folder (e.g. `posts/1.md`, `integrations/1.md`, `changelog/command-palette.md`, `legal/terms.md`, `team/david-lee.md`, `docs/getting-started/introduction.mdx`).

**Guardrail:** Adding/removing/requiring schema fields breaks pages that map `entry.data` into layouts and cards — update those together.
